<UserControl x:Class="GTAIVDowngrader.Dialogs.WelcomeUC"
             xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
             xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006" 
             xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008" 
             xmlns:local="clr-namespace:GTAIVDowngrader.Dialogs"
             mc:Ignorable="d" 
             Loaded="UserControl_Loaded"
             d:DesignHeight="634" d:DesignWidth="1050">
    
    <Grid>
        <Grid.RowDefinitions>
            <RowDefinition Height="*"/>
            <RowDefinition Height="60"/>
        </Grid.RowDefinitions>

        <!-- MainGrid -->
        <Grid x:Name="MainGrid" Grid.Row="0">
            <Grid.Triggers>
                <EventTrigger RoutedEvent="Loaded">
                    <BeginStoryboard>
                        <Storyboard>
                            <DoubleAnimation From="0.2" To="1.0" Duration="0:0:0.5" Storyboard.TargetName="MainGrid" Storyboard.TargetProperty="Opacity"/>
                        </Storyboard>
                    </BeginStoryboard>
                </EventTrigger>
            </Grid.Triggers>

            <!-- Background Char -->
            <Image Grid.RowSpan="2" Source="..\Resources\chars\char4.png" RenderOptions.BitmapScalingMode="HighQuality" Opacity="0.25" Stretch="Uniform" VerticalAlignment="Bottom" HorizontalAlignment="Right" Margin="0,61,20,-61"/>

            <!-- Content -->
            <StackPanel MaxHeight="300" HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Top" Margin="30,20">
                <TextBlock Text="Welcome to the GTA IV Downgrader!" FontSize="16" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="White" Margin="0,0,0,10"/>
                <TextBlock TextTrimming="WordEllipsis" TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="14" Foreground="White" HorizontalAlignment="Left" Margin="10,0,0,0">
                This downgrader allows you to downgrade the <Run FontWeight="Bold" Text="Steam/RGL Complete Edition (1.2.0.32 and up)"/> of GTA IV to either <Run FontWeight="Bold" Text="1.0.4.0"/>, <Run FontWeight="Bold" Text="1.0.7.0"/> or <Run FontWeight="Bold" Text="1.0.8.0"/>.
                
                <LineBreak/><LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
                <Run Text="Why should I downgrade and what are the advantages of it?" FontSize="18" FontWeight="Bold" FontStyle="Italic"/>
                
                <!-- Reason 1 -->
                <LineBreak/>
                The top and most obvious reason is for <Run Text="modding capability" FontWeight="Bold"/>. Tons of mods (especially those made <Run Text="before" FontWeight="Bold"/> 2020) only work on 1.0.8.0 or lower.
                <LineBreak/>
                For example, one of the most important mods made for the game, <Hyperlink RequestNavigate="Hyperlink_RequestNavigate" NavigateUri="https://gtaforums.com/topic/955449-iv-zolikapatch/" FontWeight="Bold">Zolika Patch</Hyperlink>, <Run Text="only" FontWeight="Bold"/> works on 1.0.8.0 or lower.
                <LineBreak/>
                Or one of the most famous mods made ever, <Hyperlink RequestNavigate="Hyperlink_RequestNavigate" NavigateUri="https://www.lcpdfr.com/lcpdfr" FontWeight="Bold">LCPDFR</Hyperlink>, works best on <Run Text="1.0.7.0" FontWeight="Bold"/>!
                
                <!-- Reason 2 -->
                <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
                The second reason is for <Run Text="stability &amp; performance" FontWeight="Bold"/>. There's utilities/mods such as <Hyperlink RequestNavigate="Hyperlink_RequestNavigate" NavigateUri="https://github.com/doitsujin/dxvk" FontWeight="Bold">DXVK</Hyperlink>, <Hyperlink RequestNavigate="Hyperlink_RequestNavigate" NavigateUri="https://github.com/elishacloud/dxwrapper" FontWeight="Bold">DxWrapper</Hyperlink>, <Hyperlink RequestNavigate="Hyperlink_RequestNavigate" NavigateUri="https://github.com/ThirteenAG/IV.EFLC.ColAccel" FontWeight="Bold">ColAccel</Hyperlink>, etc... which all work BEST on <Run Text="downgraded copies" FontWeight="Bold"/>, specifically 1.0.7.0 (Especially for DXVK)
                
                <!-- Reason 3 -->
                <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
                The third reason is for <Run Text="multiplayer" FontWeight="Bold"/>. GFWL is available on downgraded copies, and multiplayer mods such as <Hyperlink RequestNavigate="Hyperlink_RequestNavigate" NavigateUri="https://gtaconnected.com/" FontWeight="Bold">GTA Connected</Hyperlink>, <Run Text="require" FontWeight="Bold"/> a downgraded game.
                </TextBlock>
            </StackPanel>

            <CheckBox x:Name="DisableRainbowColoursCheckBox" Visibility="Collapsed" Checked="DisableRainbowColoursCheckBox_CheckedChanged" Unchecked="DisableRainbowColoursCheckBox_CheckedChanged" Content="Disable Rainbow Colours" Foreground="White" FontSize="16" 
                  HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Bottom" VerticalContentAlignment="Center" Margin="30,50"/>
            <TextBlock Text="To proceed, press the 'Next' button." FontSize="12" Foreground="#adadad" HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Bottom" Margin="30,15"/>
            <TextBlock x:Name="DowngraderVersionLabel" Text="Version 1.0" FontSize="12" Foreground="#adadad" HorizontalAlignment="Right" VerticalAlignment="Bottom" Margin="30,32"/>
            <TextBlock FontSize="12" Foreground="#adadad" HorizontalAlignment="Right" VerticalAlignment="Bottom" Margin="30,15">
            <Hyperlink x:Name="CheckForUpdatesHyperLink" Click="CheckForUpdatesHyperLink_Click" FontWeight="SemiBold">Click here to check for updates</Hyperlink>
            </TextBlock>
        </Grid>

        <!-- Bottom Grid -->
        <Rectangle Grid.Row="0" Fill="#4Dffffff" Height="1" VerticalAlignment="Bottom"/>
        <Grid x:Name="BottomGrid" Background="#B3000000" Grid.Row="1">
            <!--<Grid.Background>
                <LinearGradientBrush StartPoint="0,0.5" EndPoint="1,0.5">
                    <GradientStop Offset="0.100" Color="#B3FF0000"/>
                    <GradientStop Offset="0.1666" Color="#B3FF7F00"/>
                    <GradientStop Offset="0.450" Color="#B3FFFF00"/>
                    <GradientStop Offset="0.600" Color="#B300FF00"/>
                    <GradientStop Offset="0.7700" Color="#B30000FF"/>
                    <GradientStop Offset="0.8699" Color="#B34B0082"/>
                    <GradientStop Offset="1" Color="#B39400D3"/>
                </LinearGradientBrush>
            </Grid.Background>-->
            
            <Button x:Name="NextButton" Click="NextButton_Click" Content="Next" IsEnabled="True" Background="#0050bf" Style="{StaticResource MetroButton}" Width="80" HorizontalAlignment="Right" VerticalAlignment="Center" Margin="15,0"/>
            <Button x:Name="ExitButton" Click="ExitButton_Click" Content="Exit" IsEnabled="True" Background="#0050bf" Style="{StaticResource MetroButton}" Width="80" HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Center" Margin="15,0"/>
        </Grid>

    </Grid>
</UserControl>
